data.name: lblHelp20.ToolTip
data.value: This is the body of the email that will be sent if there is no face detected in the photo. Below are the mail body placeholders that can be used. These will be replaced when the email is sent. The mail body will accept HTML for formatting. {0} - Will be replaced with username of person. {1} - Will be replaced with the path of the image. {2} - Will be replaced with the current time. format(yyyy-MM-dd hh:mm:ss tt)

data.name: lblHelp10.ToolTip
data.value: If the photo is not square and it has already been croppped down to fit the face or the original is close up to the face then the face detection process may not keep as much of the image as possible and as a result the cropped square face may not include much of the surrounding photo context and only show a big face. Not too pretty. This option will tell the crop process to use the smallest side of the photo for cropping to a square and it will still try and put the face in the most optimal spot in the resulting image. If your photo has plenty of room around the subject then you do not need to check this.

data.name: lblHelp8.ToolTip
data.value: If the face detection feature cannot detect the face in the photo then the picture will be moved to this folder. The manual upload utility will allow you to maually resize and crop images in this folder and upload them to Confluence.

data.name: lblHelp12.ToolTip
data.value: Somtimes the face detection cannot detect a face in the image. If you are running in headless mode you can have the utility email you if it cannot find a face in the photo so that you can manually crop and upload it.
